               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Taʾammǝra Māryām "Miracles of Mary" (fols. 3ra-61vb)
 I-1) Maṣḥafa
                     śǝrʿāt, Introductory rite of al-Muʿallaqah (fols. 3ra-7rb)
 I-2)
                     Introductory exhortation and hymns (fols. 7rb-9vb)
 I-3) ʾƎsaggǝd laki
                     wa-ʾǝweddǝsaki ... "I worship Thee ..." (fols. 9vb-10va)
 I-4) Taʾammǝra
                     Māryām "Miracles of Mary": 52 miracles (fols. 11ra-61vb)
 II) Maṣḥafa ṭomār
                     "Book of the Letter (from Heaven)" (fols. 62ra-66va) 
 III) Śǝrʿāta faws
                     manfasāwi “Order of Spiritual Medicine” (fols. 66va-68va), unidentified
                     
 Additio 1.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>Text I-1 contains:</note>
                     <note>- Ṣalota za-yǝbǝl ʾǝmqǝdmä yanbǝbu täʾamriha la-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝnä Māryām ...
                        "Prayer recited before reading the Miracles of our Lady Mary ...") (<locus target="#7ra">7ra</locus>)</note>
                     <note>- Excerpt from the Gospel of John (Jn. 19:25-27) (<locus target="#7ra">7ra-</locus>rb).</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>Text I-2 includes the following hymns:</note>
                     <note>- ʾO-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä qǝddǝst dǝngǝl ba-kǝlʾe Māryām Mariham walādita ʾamlāk
                        ... "O my Lady, Holy Two-fold Virgin Mary, Godbearing ..." (<locus target="#8va">8va-</locus>vb)</note>
                     <note>- ʾO-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä qǝddǝst dǝngǝl Māryām Mariham ʾǝmmu la-ʾIyasus Krǝstos
                        kahāli ... "O my Lady, Holy Virgin Mary, Mother of Jesus Christ the Almighty
                        ..." (<locus from="8vb" to="9ra">8vb-9ra</locus> l.10)(cp. ChRep n<locus target="#373">373</locus>)</note>
                     <note>- salām laki ʾo-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä qǝddǝst dǝngǝl Māryām ʾǝmma madḫǝn wa-ʾǝmma
                        bǝrhān ... "Salutation to you, o my Lady, Holy Virgin Mary, Mother of the
                        Saviour and Mother of the Light ..." (<locus target="#9ra">9ra</locus>
                        l.10-vb).</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>Some miracles of Mary (Text I-4) are (erroneously) numbered.</note>
                     <note>The 1st and 7th miracle are followed by a hymn:</note>
                     <note>- ʾO-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä Māryām ʾǝm-beta mangǝśt wa-ʾǝm-beta kāhǝnāt ... "O my
                        Lady Mary, from the house of Kingdom and the house of Priesthood ..."
                           (<locus target="#12va">12va</locus>)</note>
                     <note>- (ʾO-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä Māryām) ḫoḫǝta mǝśrāq za-täsämäyki ... "(O my Lady
                        Mary), Threshold of the East have you been called ..." (<locus target="#20rb">20rb</locus>).</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>Text III (different from the work Maṣḥafa faws Manfasawi) is attested
                        also in Mss.<ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESdz011">DZ-011</ref>,<ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmhg006">MHG-006</ref>; it is different from Maṣḥafa faws
                        Manfasawi containede in<ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESdd016">DD-016</ref>and<ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESbgy002">BGY-002</ref>.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
